I really don't remember, but I believe in those 
early days. Before the Revolution. Before the

03:05.694 --> 03:06.515
Revolution. I guess all of it was like a farmer, you 
know. They have their little crops and all that.

03:12.883 --> 03:14.625
Did they have their own land? Well, they never did 
mention no land, but I think they were not well off.

03:22.919 --> 03:27.266
But they were, you know, just making a living 
somewhere over there in Mooskies. And so, I

03:27.286 --> 03:30.952
remember my grandfather. I remember him and my 
grandma. I remember both. And I remember when

03:34.918 --> 03:50.023
grandpa, in 1934, no, it's 1932, my 
father-in-law, my grandfather, his name was

03:34.918 --> 03:50.023
Martiniano Garza, he passed away. And I remember 
to this day, I was about six years old, but I

03:50.628 --> 04:06.104
remember that they make a casket, you know, with 
some new boars, and they put some linen, and all

03:50.628 --> 04:06.104
this means put in a wagon. And we took him, and he was 
buried over here at Snoop. No, Tunis. That's where

04:12.330 --> 04:14.973
he's buried. Then in 1934, Grandma passed away, 
and we did the same thing. And I still remember the

04:18.995 --> 04:24.900
roll and the wagon and everything. You know, the 
funerals those days, we didn't even touch no

04:25.221 --> 04:30.125
ambulance, no nothing. We just made our own 
funeral. But I remember seeing the father,

04:36.531 --> 04:41.095
because they were Catholic. I remember the father 
went and gave her the blessing. I remember that

04:44.638 --> 04:47.280
real good, because they took the father from here 
to Bryant, to the farm, and he gave all the church

04:47.615 --> 05:05.048
rights, and then she passed away that day, and then 
the father said, well, and nobody complained, and

04:47.615 --> 05:05.048
nobody said nothing, no ambulance, no nothing, 
but it was this wagon. I remember we were little. We

05:08.314 --> 05:09.977
all climbed on the wagon. And they had about four or 
five wagons, of course. All the people from the

05:12.878 --> 05:20.248
same, these men that called themselves Porres, 
they owned all those lands over there. So we took

05:20.268 --> 05:24.333
one more over there into the graveyard. But I still 
remember that this minister took part in the

05:24.353 --> 05:33.905
service of the graveyard. And he read the rights. 
But then I was seven years old. I remember then. I

05:40.315 --> 05:45.682
remember then when he got some dirt and say, ashes 
to ashes and all that. And I know that man to date,

05:46.102 --> 05:59.640
but I never had the knowledge or the thinking to 
